</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>The correspondence between <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000U.xml" title="Biinverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000U" type="local">biinvertible</fr:link> and <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-003F.xml" title="Bijection" addr="forest://erct/erct-003F" type="local">bijective</fr:link> maps of <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-003H.xml" title="Biinvertible maps are bijective" addr="forest://erct/erct-003H" type="local">Corollary <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-003H" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002Z.xml" title="Bijections are biinvertible" addr="forest://erct/erct-002Z" type="local">Corollary <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-002Z" /></fr:link> lifts to an <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000V.xml" title="Equivalence of types" addr="forest://erct/erct-000V" type="local">equivalence</fr:link> from the type of <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000V.xml" title="Equivalence of types" addr="forest://erct/erct-000V" type="local">equivalences</fr:link> to the type of <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-003F.xml" title="Bijection" addr="forest://erct/erct-003F" type="local">bijections</fr:link>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>10</fr:day></fr:date><fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-003I/0</fr:addr><fr:route>http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-003I/0.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>By <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-003G.xml" title="Being bijective is a proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-003G" type="local">Corollary <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-003G" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002S.xml" title="Being biinvertible is a proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-002S" type="local">Corollary <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-002S" /></fr:link> via <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-003D.xml" title="Path object comprehension" addr="forest://erct/erct-003D" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-003D" /></fr:link>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
              <fr:month>12</fr:month>
              <fr:day>20</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-001D</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001D.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="The univalence principle for types">The univalence principle for types</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Axiom</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001D.agda" type="external">erct-001D.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>The <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-004B.xml" title="Reflexive graph" addr="forest://erct/erct-004B" type="local">reflexive graph</fr:link> structure on types given by <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000V.xml" title="Equivalence of types" addr="forest://erct/erct-000V" type="local">equivalences</fr:link> is <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0010.xml" title="Path object" addr="forest://erct/erct-0010" type="local">univalent</fr:link>. We shall write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {Type}]]></fr:tex> to indicate the resulting (large) path object of types and <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000V.xml" title="Equivalence of types" addr="forest://erct/erct-000V" type="local">equivalences</fr:link>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
              <fr:month>12</fr:month>
              <fr:day>3</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-000L/0</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000L/0.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="The univalence principle for precategories › "><fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000L.xml" title="The univalence principle for precategories" addr="forest://erct/erct-000L" type="local">The univalence principle for <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000B.xml" title="Precategory" addr="forest://erct/erct-000B" type="local">precategories</fr:link></fr:link> › </fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
  <html:p>The type of isomorphisms onto <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> is inhabited, considering the identity isomorphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1_{C}\colon  C\cong  C]]></fr:tex>. Therefore, it suffices to show that the type of <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000J.xml" title="Isomorphism of precategories" addr="forest://erct/erct-000J" type="local">isomorphisms</fr:link> onto <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> depicted below is a <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>:</html:p>

  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
   \begin {aligned}
    D &: \mathsf {Precategory}\\
    F &: D\cong  C
   \end {aligned}
  ]]></fr:tex>

  <html:p>We unfold the definitions of a <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000B.xml" title="Precategory" addr="forest://erct/erct-000B" type="local">precategories</fr:link> and <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000J.xml" title="Isomorphism of precategories" addr="forest://erct/erct-000J" type="local">their isomorphisms</fr:link>, dropping <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">propositional</fr:link> axioms:</html:p>

  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    \begin {aligned}
      D_0&: \mathsf {Type}\\
      D_1&:D_0\to  D_0\to \mathsf {Set}\\
      F_0&: D_0\to  C_0\\
      F_1&: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} D_1xy\to  C
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen F_0x,F_0y\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\\
      h_1 &: \mathsf {isBiinvertible}\,F_0\\
      h_2 &: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} \mathsf {isPropMap}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen F_1xy\right \rparen \mathclose {}

      \\
      h_3 &: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} \mathsf {isSurjection}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen F_1xy\right \rparen \mathclose {}

    \end {aligned}
  ]]></fr:tex>

  <html:p>A function that is both <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="forest://erct/erct-001T" type="local">propositional</fr:link> and a <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0029.xml" title="Surjection" addr="forest://erct/erct-0029" type="local">surjection</fr:link>, i.e. a <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-003F.xml" title="Bijection" addr="forest://erct/erct-003F" type="local">bijection</fr:link>, is an <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000V.xml" title="Equivalence of types" addr="forest://erct/erct-000V" type="local">equivalence</fr:link> by <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002Z.xml" title="Bijections are biinvertible" addr="forest://erct/erct-002Z" type="local">Corollary <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-002Z" /></fr:link>. We can therefore repackage our telescope equivalently:</html:p>

  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    \begin {aligned}
      D_0&: \mathsf {Type}\\
      D_1&:D_0\to  D_0\to \mathsf {Set}\\
      F_0&: D_0\cong  C_0\\
      F_1&: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} D_1xy\cong  C
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen F_0x,F_0y\right \rparen \mathclose {}

    \end {aligned}
  ]]></fr:tex>

  <html:p>By the univalence principle for types, we may contract 
 <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen D_0,F_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
 to 
 <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen 
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
, 1_{
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
}\right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
:</html:p>

  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    \begin {aligned}
      D_1&:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\to  
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\to \mathsf {Set}\\
      F_1&: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} D_1xy\cong  C
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\right \rparen \mathclose {}

    \end {aligned}
  ]]></fr:tex>

  <html:p>Next we rewrite using the univalence principles for functions and families of types (<fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0015.xml" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions" addr="forest://erct/erct-0015" type="local">Axiom <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-0015" /></fr:link>, <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001D.xml" title="The univalence principle for types" addr="forest://erct/erct-001D" type="local">Axiom <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-001D" /></fr:link>):</html:p>

  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    \begin {aligned}
      D_1&:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\to  
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\to \mathsf {Set}\\
      F_1&: D_1 = \lambda {x,y}\mathpunct {.}{C
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}
    \end {aligned}
  ]]></fr:tex>

  <html:p>By the <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0015.xml" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions" addr="forest://erct/erct-0015" type="local">univalence principle for functions</fr:link>, the data above is <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001H.xml" title="Contractible type" addr="forest://erct/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
